NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS

- System development uses an agile approach.
- The system is implemented using the Java programming language using a Test-Driven Development (TDD) approach regarding
code development.
- A minimum of 95% of code coverage and mutation coverage (80%) of tests is required. (UI and IO packages are not
included in this coverage requirements.)
- All code, comments and documentation are in English.
- System’s documentation is in the project’s Bitbucket wiki.
- A text console UI is available for local system management by the Administrator.
- In the early stages of development, the other users use a text console to interact with the system.
- The UI is in English.
- All data exchange between controller and UI classes will use DTOs, in order to improve application's
serviceability